name: Sant Climent de Taüll VR
summary: The Church of Sant Climent de Taüll, built in the 12th century, is the prototype of a Romanesque basilica-plan church and the origin of one of the most famous mural paintings in history, the Christ in Majesty of Taüll. It is part of the group of Romanesque churches in the Vall de Boí, recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage Site since the year 2000.
